reviewText:
Netplay is about as ♥♥♥♥♥♥ as the PS3 port of this game. Still solid overall, but a real bummer that it's basically unplayable if you take it online.

// The below was written before the game had been patched.//

Important to note, after testing a PS3 TE Round 2, and PS3 Hori HRAP v3, Ps3 sticks do not seem to work very well with this port. It does not allow you to use the D-Pad" setting

I'm a huge fan of the series but I absolutely can't recommend this poor pc porn cause of the side screen fillers;
Yes I understand that the game was launched around 2012, but back then games on wide screen still existed so there shouldn't be an excuse for sloppy port in 2015!
Arc System Works just wanted a quick fix money grab, rather to obtain huge profits from an un-tapped market that is the pc gaming;
They focus only on consoles and after 3 or more years we might get a release on pcs, a release that no one gives a **** about, none other than the fans of the series that even if they buy it they are betrayed by poor porting.

In the end what I would recommend, is think well before buying a great game with bad port, I for one couldn't accept this and I chose a refund for it.
